@NODE "Einf" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{i}DTConvert@{ui} converts picture-@{"datatypes" LINK "Datatypes"} (JPEG, GIF, PCX etc.)
into IFF-ILBM-pictures and forces IFF-compatible programs to load datatypes.

So many old programs (e.g. DPaint) can use datatypes.

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

Simply copy @{i}DTConvert@{ui} into the WBStartup-drawer of your workbench.
@{i}DTConvert@{ui} will be run automaticly at every startup.

Of course you can run @{i}DTConvert@{ui} from CLI/Shell, too:

@{b}RUN DTConvert@{ub}

and remove it:

@{b}RUN DTConvert QUIT@{ub}

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Vor" "System requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}DTConvert requires:@{ub}

 ñ OS 3.0 (v39) or better
 ñ 2 MB RAM (depends on the programs and datatypes)
 ñ installed picture-datatypes (ILBM,GIF,PCX,TIFF etc.)


@{b}Not neccessary, but recommanded:@{ub}

 ñ 4 MB RAM
 ñ 68020 processor
 ñ Harddisk
 ñ Datatypes, that can also save!

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Kompak" "Compatibility"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{i}DTConvert@{ui} has been tested with the following programs using OS3.1 and 6MB RAM:

@{b}
 ñ DPaintIV AGA
 ñ Databench
 ñ Doscontrol
 ñ MainActor
 ñ Adorage
 ñ TurboPrint Professional 3
 ñ MaxonMULTIMEDIA
 ñ Imagine 2
 ñ Reflections
 ñ XiPaint 3.2
 ...@{ub}


As @{i}DTConvert@{ui} patches the DOS functions Open() and Lock(), it can interfere with
with other programs like SnoopDOS.

DTConvert can only be called once - so please don't try to convert several pictures at
one time.

Of course you require some picture datatypes (including ILBM) in the drawer "Devs/Datatypes".

@{i}DTConvert@{ui} doesn't patch OpenFromLock(). So programs that uses this function won't
run correctly. But I don't think there will be many (I don't know one).

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Konfig" "Getting started"
@TOC "MAIN"

You can run @{i}DTConvert@{ui} either from Workbench or Shell.

DTConvert will be added as an commodity, so you can control it with the program
@{i}Exchange@{ui} oder call it via HotKey (try @{b}left alt d@{ub}).

If you run @{i}DTConvert@{ui} twice a control window is opened:

@{b}Pattern:@{ub}     please enter here an AmigaDOS pattern for picture files.
.                     @{i}DTConvert@{ui} only converts files that matches this pattern.
                      If DTConvert won't work, first check this field.
                      By entering "#?" DTConvert will check every file. WARNING: this will
                      slow down your system.

@{b}buffer:@{ub}          this is an temporary buffer file, where @{i}DTConvert@{ui}
                      saves the converted picture. If you haven't enough RAM try to
                      save this file to your harddisk ("hd0:t/DTPatch.data")

@{b}Save datatype:@{ub}    you can choose other datatypes to save
                      Of course they have to support saving (OM_WRITE).
                      --- NOT SUPPORTED YET ---


@{b}Requester on...@{ub}    @{i}DTConvert@{ui} can open requesters either on
                      workbench or active screen.
                      WARNING: "Active screen" is a system hack and not 100% system compactible.

@{b} DOS.Open patched@{ub}   @{i}DTConvert@{ui} patches Open()

@{b} DOS.Lock patched@{ub}   Some programs (e.g. DosControl) uses the
                      Lock() funktion to get the size of a file. Then you have to
                      activate this point.

@{b} Request: Convert@{ub}    @{i}DTConvert@{ui} will ask every time, whether to convert
                      this file or not.

@{b} Only selected tasks:@{ub}    Choose which tasks @{i}DTConvert@{ui} shall work with.
                      Click on @{b}Select@{ub} and choose from the list of active tasks.

Of course you can control @{i}DTConvert@{ui} via shell parameters or workbench tooltypes:


@{b}QUIT@{ub}             forces @{i}DTConvert@{ui} to quit.

@{b}GUI@{ub}              opens the control window.

@{b}PATTERN="..."@{ub}    this is the file pattern (explained above)

@{b}TEMPFILE="..."@{ub}   the temporary file (explained above)

@{b}DONTPATCHOPEN@{ub}    don't patch Open() function

@{b}DONTPATCHLOCK@{ub}    don't patch Lock() function

@{b}QUIET@{ub}            be quiet..

@{b}CX_POPKEY@{ub}        DTConvert will be added as an Commodity to your system.
                          So you can enter a hotkey to call DTConvert's control window.
                          (e.g. "lalt d")
@{"Back" LINK "Main"}

@ENDNODE

